-- Shares in Banca Carige up more than 2 pct on asset sale speculation 
-- By Francesca Landini
-- Tue Jul 22, 2014 03:14AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 22 (Reuters) - Shares in Italy's Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> rose after a media report saying the mid-sized lender's board would discuss on Tuesday a bid for its insurance assets presented by German insurer Talanx <TLXGn.DE>.

According to daily Il Messaggero, the bank aims to cash in 400 million euros from the sale of its insurance units.